 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Tue, 02 Dec 2025 16:25:22 +0100

rust-proxmox-access-control (1.3.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * add acl feature to only expose types and the AclTree, which can be useful,
    when an application wants to only handle an acl tree without depending on
    more complex features provided by the rest of the `impl` feature or its
    bigger dependencies (e.g. openssl).

  * move functions querying privileges to the AclTree, making them accessible
    to the new acl feature.

  * derive Debug and PartialEq on AclTree and AclTreeNode.

  * allow one to opt-into reading all ACLs of the current authid, even if they
    come from groups.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Wed, 19 Nov 2025 19:37:09 +0100

